  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nbuilt from bit repo\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI am currently attempting to run a project that works correctly under a hardhat node under anvil, and am not succeeding.\r\n\r\nAfter augmenting InvalidTransactionError::GasTooHigh to be a struct that allows me to report details as to which GasTooHigh instance is being generated, the failing call seems to be from In `pub fn call_with_state<D>`. Therein it looks to me like every EvmError, irrespective of its actual type, is reported as a GastTooHigh error.\r\n\r\nIs this intentional?\r\n",
